    overview: `The Dolomites are the most visually dramatic cycling destination on the planet. UNESCO World Heritage roads wind between rose-pink vertical towers of rock, crossing passes above 2,000m that appear on almost every serious cyclist's bucket list: Passo Gardena, Passo Sella, Passo Pordoi, the Stelvio. The Sellaronda loop — four passes in a single day — is one of the defining rides in cycling. Road quality is exceptional, altitude is genuinely challenging (plan for slower speeds than at sea level), and June-September is the only viable window before snow closes the passes.`,

